ado-city-housing-growth-caps" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/03/kids-camp-cyberstalk-empty-nest" target="_blank">With my kids away, I’m expected to relax – but I’m too busy cyberstalking them | Emma Brockes</a></h2><div class="description"> I once scoffed at the idea of ‘empty nest syndrome’ Now I scour camp photos like a homicide detective, on the lookout for scowls or sunburn. Single parenting, in the absence of immediate family, can feel like being one person.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 07:00:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/03/kids-camp-cyberstalk-empty-nest" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/03/shoplifting-crime-poverty-prisons-tories-law-and-order" target="_blank">In a broken Britain, the Tories zero in on shoplifters stealing Calpol and food for their children | Owen Jones</a></h2><div class="description"> Ministers’ threats to send culprits to prison will never solve them. The Tories’ plan to cling on to power is now abundantly cle cleared. You’re 23 times more likely to be prosecuted for benefit fraud than tax fraud, even though the latter costs the economy nine times more.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 09:00:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="